Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
report_metal_fill(25.10)                              report_metal_fill(25.10)

Name
       report_metal_fill  -  Generates a report on metal fill to summarize the
       number and area of fill shapes on a per-net and per-layer basis

Syntax
       report_metal_fill

       [-help]

       [-file <file_name>]

       [-fill_area]

       [-fill_length]

       [-mesh]

       Generates a report on metal fill to summarize the number  and  area  of
       fill  shapes on a per-net and per-layer basis. Use the generated report
       to tune the add_metal_fill_signoff flow parameters to achieve  the  de-
       sired  distribution across multiple nets and layers as well as to mini-
       mize floating fill.

       Before generating a metal fill report, you should have:

              * Imported the design

              * Completed detailed routing

              * Added metal fill

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each report_metal_fill parameter.

              For  a  detailed  description of the command and all its parame-
              ters, use man report_metal_fill.

       -file <file_name>
              Writes the report to a file with the specified name.

              Default: <topCellName>_metal_fill_report.rpt

       -fill_area
              Reports area information for metal fill for each layer.

       -fill_length
              Reports length information for metal fill for each layer.

       -mesh  Reports mesh information for  metal fill.

Examples
              * The following command  writes  a  metal  fill  report  to  the
                dtmf_metal_fill.rpt file.

                report_metal_fill -file dtmf_metal_fill.rpt

                The output is as follows:

